description: Gentle upper body stretches for your workday

instructions.text: Tilt your ear toward the shoulder opposite the side you want to stretch, then look down toward the floor.
Place the hand on the side you tilted toward on top of your head and gently pull toward your collarbone.
Hold as prescribed and then repeat.
You should feel this stretch in the back and side of your neck.
Placing your free hand behind your back at waist height will intensify the stretch.

exercise.description: Reach across body with arm horizontal

instructions.text: Begin standing or sitting up tall.
Reach arm across body, use the opposite hand to pull arm closer for a stretch.
Hold and return to starting position.
You should feel a stretch near the back of your shoulder.

exercise.name: Stretch Shoulder Horizontal Adduction

instructions.text: Begin in a comfortable seated or standing position.
Bring your ear on the affected side to your shoulder and gently press with your hand for an increased stretch.
You should feel this stretch on the side of your neck.
Gently grasp affected hand at the fingers with opposite hand.
Move back of hand up toward elbow, using opposite hand to provide additional stretch at the end of the motion.
Return to start position.
You should feel a stretch in your hand and the bottom side of your forearm.
Sit or stand up straight.
Rotate your head to the prescribed side.
Gently push your chin with your fingers to assist the stretch.
Hold and release.
You should feel this stretch on the side that your head is turned towards, and specifically near the back side of your neck.
Begin gently grasping affected hand with opposite hand.
Move palm toward elbow using opposite hand to provide additional stretch at the end of the motion.
Return to start position.
You should feel a stretch on the top side of your forearm.

exercise.description: Reach away from body with arm horiztonal

instructions.text: Begin standing in a doorway with elbow bent and arm lifted to shoulder height and pressed against the door frame.
Shift body forward into the doorway for a stretch.
Hold as prescribed and return to start position
You should feel a stretch in your chest muscles and front of your shoulder.

exercise.name: Stretch Shoulder Horizontal Abduction

name: Office Friendly Upper Quarter Stretches
